	('Dwi Pada Viprarita Dandasana', '177', 'Dwi PÄda ViparÄ«ta Dáº¡á¹‡dÄsana', 'Final: 516 | Int: 514, 515, 517, 518, 519, 520', 24, false, NULL, NULL, 'Lie flat on your back and bend your knees, bringing your feet close to your buttocks. Bend your elbows and turn your wrists to place your palms on the floor near your shoulders with fingers outstretched. On an exhalation, lift your buttocks and back off the floor to rest the crown of your head on the ground. Lift your right arm and place your hand behind your head, resting the elbow and forearm on the floor, then repeat with the left hand. Interlock your fingers so your head is cupped as if in a headstand.

Press both forearms firmly into the ground, raise your buttocks higher, and extend your legs one at a time until they are straight and together. Remain in this final position for 30 to 60 seconds with normal breathing, eventually building up to five minutes. Ensure your forearms and elbows remain firmly grounded, your chest is broad, your buttocks are tight, and your spine is tucked in to prevent the feet from slipping. To exit, walk your feet back in, unlock your fingers, and place your palms near your shoulders. Exhale as you carefully lower your trunk to the floor and lie flat.

