	('Samakonasana', '170', 'Samaká»nÄsana', 'Final: 477', 38, false, 354, 296, 'Be seated on the yoga mat. Keep your legs straight and extended in front of you. Slowly inhale and lengthen your spine. Keep your head to buttocks in one line. Engage your core. As you exhale, split your legs wide apart. Exhale and bend forward from your hips slowly. Lower your upper body until it is parallel to the ground. Keep your legs straight with a very slight bend at the knees. Do not hunch your back. Keep your spine straight. Gaze forward.', '09_Backbends', NULL, NULL, 'Straight Angle Pose', '14/2/2026 4:12pm', 'Samakonasana
Sama means the same, like, even or straight. Kona means an angle and a point of a compass. In this asana the split is performed with the legs spread apart sideways, and the hands are folded in front of the chest. It is harder to perform than Hanumanasana. (Image 475.) Both the legs and the pelvic region of the body are in one straight line.

Technique

Stand in Tadasana (Image 1), rest the hands on the hips and spread the legs apart sideways to your capacity. (Image 29)

Place the palms on the floor (Image 30) and with an exhalation stretch the legs further and further until you sit on the floor with both legs spread sideways in a straight line. The entire back of the legs, especially the back of the knees, should rest on the floor.

Join the palms in front of the chest (Image 477) and stay in the pose for a few seconds.

Place the palms on the floor, raise the hips and bring the legs closer and closer to each other until you stand up again in Uttanasana. (Image 47.) Then stand in Tadasana (Image 1) and relax.

Effects: In this pose the hip joints are exercised and the legs are made to move freely in all directions. The spine is stretched and any defect in the lower part of the spine is cured. The pose, like Hanumanasana (Image 475), tones the leg muscles and makes the legs shapely. It prevents the development of hernia and relieves sciatic pains. It helps the blood to circulate in the pelvic region and genital organs and keeps them healthy.', true, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'à¤¸à¤®à¤•à¥‹à¤£à¤¾à¤¸à¤¨', 'sama (equal, straight) + kona (angle) + asana (pose); pose of equal angles', 'This pose depends on the equal and opposing actions of the adductors, countered by hamstring and quadriceps engagement to maintain spinal extension from the sacrum.', 'Two parallel lines, representing the legs, flank an open circle positioned midway between them, symbolizing the core''s stabilizing action.', true, '/storage/v1/object/public/yoga-cards/170_master_samakonasana.webp', '/storage/v1/object/public/audio-assets/170_samakonasana.mp3', NULL, NULL, 3, '{"flow": 5, "long": 120, "short": 30, "standard": 60}', '[]', false),
