	('Uddiyana Bandha', '201', 'Uá¸á¸Ä«yÄna Bandha', 'Final: 593, 594', 12, false, NULL, 356, 'Stand in the mountain pose with the feet parallel. Spread the legs about one foot apart. Stoop the torso slightly forward and bend both knees. Spread the fingers wide. Grip the middle of the thighs firmly with the hands. Bend the arms slightly at the elbows. Lower the chin as far down as possible to form the chin lock (Jalandhara Bandha). Inhale deeply through the nose. Exhale quickly so the air is expelled from the lungs in a single rush. Hold the breath without allowing any inhalation. Pull the whole abdominal region back towards the spine. Lift the abdominal muscles upwards toward the diaphragm. Keep the chest broad without hollowing it. Raise the lumbar and dorsal spine forwards and upwards. Squeeze the abdominal organs towards the back of the body. Press the organs firmly against the spine. Lift the hands from the thighs while maintaining the abdominal grip. Rest the hands higher on the pelvic rim. Press the hands into the pelvic rim to create a firmer contraction. Straighten the back while keeping the abdominal grip tight. Keep the chin lowered in the chin lock (Jalandhara Bandha). Hold the grip for ten to fifteen seconds. Avoid holding the breath beyond the limit of endurance. Relax the abdominal muscles first without moving the chin or the head. Allow the abdomen to return to its normal relaxed position. Inhale slowly and quietly. Refrain from any inhalation during the contraction and holding phases. Take a few normal breaths to recover. Repeat the entire cycle not more than six to eight times at a single stretch. Practice this sequence once a day only. Master this standing technique before introducing the abdominal lock (Uddiyana Bandha) into seated pranayama during the interval after exhalation.', '10_Restorative_Pranayama', NULL, NULL, 'Abdominal Lift', '14/2/2026 4:12pm', 'Uddiyana Bandha
