	('Eka Pada Rajakapotasana II', '186', 'Eka PÄda RÄjakapotÄsana II', 'Final: 545', 29, true, 392, 325, 'Begin in a low lunge position. Place the right leg bent in front. Keep the right knee over the ankle. Extend the left leg behind you. Rest the left knee on the floor. Inhale and lift the torso upward. Prepare for a backbend. Raise the left lower leg. Bring the left foot within reach. Reach back with the left arm. Grasp the left foot. Keep the chest lifted. Relax the shoulders. Push the hips gently downward. Push the torso gently upward. To release, bring the head back to the center. Release the hands one after the other. Lower the back leg to the ground. Tuck the back toes under. Lift the hips. Align the body in Adho Mukha Svanasana.', '09_Backbends', NULL, NULL, 'One-Legged King Pigeon Pose II', '14/2/2026 4:12pm', 'Eka Pada Rajakapotasana II or King pigeon II
