	('Mulabhandasana', '165', 'MÅ«labhandÄsana', 'Final: 462, 463 | Int: 459, 460, 461', 32, false, 344, 286, 'Begin by aligning to Bound Angle Pose. Gradually bring the feet near the groins. Slowly tilt the calf muscles outwards with assistance from the hands. Slowly lift the hips off the floor. Place the arms on the floor as support. Place the feet so the soles and heels touch each other. Rest the hips and be seated. Turn the feet by grasping the toes. Point the toes straight downwards. Point the heels upwards. Place the hands near the groins. Keep the spine alert. Exhale completely. Tighten the anus for the root lock. Pull the abdomen in for the abdominal lock. Lock the chin to the neck for the chin lock. Keep the perineum tight. Stay with breath retention. Release the root lock first. Release the abdominal lock next. Release the chin lock last. Inhale after the chin lock release. Release the foot alignment. Release the legs gradually.', '08_Advanced_Leg_behind_Head', NULL, NULL, 'Root Lock Pose', '14/2/2026 4:12pm', 'Mulabhandasana or Root lock.
