	('Padahasthasana', '019', 'PÄda HastÄsana', 'Final: 46 | Int: 45', 6, false, 91, 64, 'Stand in Tadasana. Spread the legs a foot apart. Exhale and bend forward. Do not bend the legs at the knees. Insert the hands under the feet. The palms should touch the soles. Keep the head up. Make the back as concave as possible. Do not slacken the grip at the knees. Take a few breaths in this position. Now exhale. Move the head in between the knees. Bend the elbows. Pull the feet up from the palms. Stay in the pose for about twenty seconds with normal breathing. Inhale and raise the head. Come back to the position with the head well up. Take two breaths. Inhale and stand up. Return to Tadasana.', '01_Standing_and_Basic', NULL, NULL, 'Hand Under Foot Pose', '14/2/2026 4:12pm', 'Padahasthasana
