	('Parighasana', '015', 'ParighÄsana', 'Final: 39 | Int: 37, 38', 4, true, 85, 60, 'Kneel on the floor with your ankles together. Stretch the right leg sideways to the right. Keep the right leg in line with the trunk and the left knee. Turn the right foot sideways to the right. Keep the right leg stiff at the knee. Extend the arms sideways with an inhalation. Take two breaths. Exhale and move the trunk and right arm down towards the extended right leg. Rest the right forearm on the right shin. Rest the right wrist on the right ankle. The right palm faces up. The right ear rests on the right upper arm. Move the left arm over the head. Touch the right palm with the left hand. The left ear touches the left upper arm. Stay in this position for thirty to sixty seconds. Breathe normally. Inhale and move the trunk and arms back to the starting position. Bend the right leg. Kneel on the floor. Keep the ankles together again. Repeat the pose on the other side. Substitute the right side for the left side and vice versa. Stay in the pose on both sides for the same amount of time.', '01_Standing_and_Basic', NULL, NULL, 'Gate Pose', '14/2/2026 4:12pm', 'Parighasana or Gate Pose
