	('Ardha Baddha Padmottanasana', '022', 'Ardha Baddha PadmottÄnÄsana', 'Final: 52, 53, 54, 55 | Int: 50, 51 Intermediate: Intermediate:', 9, true, NULL, NULL, 'Stand in Tadasana. Inhale and raise the right leg from the floor. Bend the right knee. Rest the sole of the right foot on the left thigh. Hold the right foot with the left hand. Bring the right arm around the back. Catch the big toe of the right foot with the thumb, fore, and middle fingers of the right hand. Release the left hand. Exhale and bend the trunk forward. Place the left hand on the floor by the left foot. Keep the head up. Make the back as concave as possible. Take a few breaths. Exhale and rest the head or chin on the left knee. If the whole left palm cannot be placed on the floor, start with the tips of the fingers. Gradually place the fingers on the floor. Finally, place the whole palm on the floor. Repeat these steps on the other side.', '01_Standing_and_Basic', '', NULL, 'Half Bound Lotus Standing Forward Bend', '14/2/2026 4:12pm', 'Ardha Baddha Padmottanasana
