	('Supta Trivikramasana', '171', 'Supta TrivikramÄsana', 'Final: 478', 39, true, 356, 297, 'Begin the practice from a seated pose, Dandasana. Press the heels firmly. Point the toes downwards. Lie back on the floor. Inhale and raise the right leg to ninety degrees. Hold the big toe with your right hand. Push the left thigh down with your left hand. Slowly pull the right leg down behind your head. Place the big toe to the floor. Release the pose slowly. Repeat the actions with the left leg.', '09_Backbends', NULL, NULL, 'Reclining Trivikrama Pose', '14/2/2026 4:12pm', 'Supta Trivikramasana or Vishnu''s stride (reclining)
The technique involves lying flat, pulling one leg down behind the head, and touching the big toe to the floor.
