	('Marichyasana IV', '115', 'MarÄ«chyÄsana IV', 'Final: 305, 306', 11, true, 257, 208, 'Begin seated in Dandasana. Extend both legs straight in front. Ground the sitting bones evenly. Lengthen the spine. Place one leg in half lotus. Bend the opposite knee. Bring the sole of the foot flat to the floor. Keep the foot close to the sitting bone. Inhale and lengthen the spine. Exhale and twist the torso towards the bent knee. Wrap the arm around the shin of the bent knee. Sweep the opposite arm around the back. Clasp the hands behind the back. Hold the pose for a few breaths. Release the bind. Straighten the bent leg.', '06_Twists', NULL, NULL, 'Marichiâ€™s Pose IV', '14/2/2026 4:12pm', 'Marichyasana IV
This pose is a seated twist, which includes one leg in half lotus and the opposite knee bent up, with the hands clasped behind the back.
