	('Eka Pada Urdhva Dhanurasana', '174', 'Eka PÄda Åªrdhva DhanurÄsana', 'Final: 501, 502 | Int: 500', 12, true, 365, 304, 'Lie flat on your back. Bend your knees. Place your feet flat on the floor. Keep your feet hip-width apart. Place your hands beside your head. Keep your palms wide. Press through your feet. Lift your hips toward the ceiling. Push through your hands. Lift your chest. Enter Wheel Pose (Urdhva Dhanurasana). Center one leg for stability. Mindfully lift the other leg. Draw the knee to the chest. Straighten the leg toward the ceiling. Contract the thigh muscle. Reach through the ball of the raised foot. Maintain balance on one hand and one foot.', '09_Backbends', NULL, NULL, 'One-Legged Upward Bow Pose', '14/2/2026 4:12pm', 'Eka Pada Urdhva Dhanurasana or One-leg wheel.', true, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'à¤à¤•à¤ªà¤¾à¤¦à¤Šà¤°à¥à¤§à¥à¤µà¤§à¤¨à¥à¤°à¤¾à¤¸à¤¨', 'Eka (one), Pada (foot), Urdhva (upward), Dhanura (bow), Asana (pose).', 'This pose integrates single leg balance with a deep backbend, demanding precise spinal extension and engagement of the standing leg''s adductors to maintain stability. The lifted leg increases the pose''s difficulty, testing core strength and hamstring flexibility.', 'A square frame contains a diagonal slash that ascends from the bottom left to the top right, representing spinal extension. An open circle intersects the slash, offset towards the upper right corner of the frame, symbolizing the single supporting leg and its balancing act.', true, '/storage/v1/object/public/yoga-cards/174_master_eka_pada_urdhva_dhanurasana.webp', '/storage/v1/object/public/audio-assets/174_ekapadaurdhvadhanurasana.mp3', NULL, NULL, 9, '{"flow": 5, "long": 30, "short": 20, "standard": 25}', '[]', false),
