Effects: Dorsal region fully extended, Pelvic joints become elastic, Intense chest expansion, benefits thyroids.', true, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'à¤¸à¥à¤ªà¥à¤¤à¤µà¤œà¥à¤°à¤¾à¤¸à¤¨', 'Reclined Thunderbolt Pose', 'In Supta Vajrasana, the quadriceps lengthen intensely as the knees flex towards the floor, while the abdominal muscles engage to lift the frontal iliac spines towards the sternum, preserving lumbar curve. The psoas muscles lengthen eccentrically to allow the thighs to open in external rotation.', 'The symbol features an offset vertical axis crossed by concentric arcs that suggest the opening of the hips and engagement of the core in the pose.', true, '/storage/v1/object/public/yoga-cards/057_master_supta_vajrasana.webp', '/storage/v1/object/public/audio-assets/057_suptavajrasana.mp3', NULL, NULL, 9, '{"flow": 5, "long": 120, "short": 30, "standard": 60}', '[]', false),
	('Akarna Dhanurasana', '073', 'Ä€kaá¹›na DhanurÄsana', 'Final: 173, 175 | Int: 172, 174', 11, true, 177, 141, 'Sit on the floor with the legs stretched straight in front in dandasana. Press the heels and the backs of the knees firmly into the mat. Lift the sides of the waist and the chest vertically. Reach forward and hold the right big toe between the right thumb and the index and middle fingers. Hold the left big toe with the left thumb and the index and middle fingers in the same manner. Keep the spinal column erect and the legs fully extended. Exhale and bend the left elbow to lift the left foot. Bend the left knee and bring the leg upward. Take one breath. Exhale and pull the left foot toward the head until the heel rests near the left ear. Draw the left arm back from the shoulder as if pulling a bow string. Maintain a firm grip on the right big toe. Keep the right leg straight and pinned to the floor. Ensure the back of the right knee does not lift. Hold this position for fifteen to twenty seconds while breathing normally. Exhale and stretch the left leg up vertically toward the ceiling. Take one breath. Exhale and draw the straightened left leg further back until the calf touches the left ear. Grip both big toes firmly throughout the movement. Extend both legs fully without bending the knees. Balance the trunk and the head in this vertical stretch. Remain in this position for ten to fifteen seconds with normal breathing. Exhale and bend the left knee to bring the left heel back to the left ear. Lower the left leg carefully to the floor. Stretch both legs straight in front in the starting position. Repeat the entire process on the right side by pulling the right foot toward the right ear. Raise the right leg vertically while the left leg remains straight on the floor. Maintain the pose on the right side for an equal length of time. Release the grip on the big toes. Relax the arms and legs completely.', '03_Forward_Bends', NULL, NULL, 'Archer Pose', '14/2/2026 4:12pm', 'Akarna Dhanurasana or Archer Pose

The name is derived from the Sanskrit word karna which means ear and the prefix a which means toward or near. Dhanu translates to a bow. The posture describes the physical action of pulling the foot near the ear which resembles an archer pulling back a bow string to its full extent.

Effects: adjusts minor hip deformities, exercises the lower spine, aids bowel movement.', true, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'à¤†à¤•à¤°à¥à¤£ à¤§à¤¨à¥à¤°à¤¾à¤¸à¤¨', 'Drawing-to-the-Ear Bow Pose', 'Akarna Dhanurasana powerfully stretches the hamstrings and hip abductors of one leg while simultaneously engaging the hip flexors of the opposite leg; the pose requires deep external rotation of the hip of the ''bowstring'' leg and the active lifting of the frontal iliac spines to maintain the integrity of the lumbar curve.', 'A bow with an arrow pulled back to the ear. The bow is represented by a thin, elegant line, and a solid bindu marks the point of focus.', true, '/storage/v1/object/public/yoga-cards/073_master_akarna_dhanurasana.webp', '/storage/v1/object/public/audio-assets/073_akarnadhanurasana.mp3', NULL, NULL, 3, '{"flow": 5, "long": 60, "short": 15, "standard": 30}', '[]', false),
	('Baddha Hasta Sirsasana', '078', 'Baddha Hasta ÅšÄ«á¹›sÄsana', 'Final: 198', 4, false, 193, 155, 'Begin in a kneeling position. Place your forearms on the mat. Fold your arms. Catch your upper arms with your hands. Place the crown of your head on a blanket. Position the blanket beyond your forearms. Tuck your toes. Straighten your legs. Walk your feet in towards your head. Engage your core. Pull your legs up toward the ceiling. Press your elbows into the ground. Press your shoulder girdle down. Suck your ribs in. Point your feet. Maintain the balance. Switch the hand grip. Maintain balance on your head. Bend at your waist. Exhale. Jump back to Chaturanga Dandasana.', '04_Inversions_Sirsasana_Sarvangasana', NULL, NULL, 'Bound Hands Headstand', '14/2/2026 4:12pm', 'Baddha Hasta Sirsasana or Bound hand headstand
This posture involves folding the arms, catching the upper arms, placing the crown of the head on a blanket beyond the forearms, and pulling the legs up.
Effects: Puts strain on neck, eventually brings lightness, Builds spinal and neck strength.', true, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'à¤¬à¤¦à¥à¤§à¤¹à¤¸à¥à¤¤à¤¶à¥€à¤°à¥à¤·à¤¾à¤¸à¤¨', '"Bound Hands Headstand Pose": baddha (bound), hasta (hand), shirsha (head), asana (pose).', 'Forearms create a stable triangular base. Interlocked hands cup the head, providing support while maintaining spinal alignment and preventing neck compression.', 'An offset vertical axis represents the weight-bearing spinal line. Concentric arcs emanate from the base of the axis and extend asymmetrically, depicting stability while inverted. A solid bindu sits atop the vertical axis, symbolizing the concentrated dristi.', true, '/storage/v1/object/public/yoga-cards/078_master_baddha_hasta_sirsasana.webp', '/storage/v1/object/public/audio-assets/078_baddhahastasirsasana.mp3', NULL, NULL, 4, '{"flow": 5, "long": 120, "short": 30, "standard": 60}', '[]', false),
	('Setu Bandhasana', '111', 'Setu Bandhasana', 'Final: 296 | Int: 293, 294, 295', 14, false, 249, 202, 'Lie on your back. Bend your knees toward the ceiling. Place the soles of your feet flat on the mat. Keep your feet hip-width apart. Reach down with your fingertips to skim your heels. Press into the soles of your feet. Lift your pelvis away from the floor. Arch your trunk. Tuck your shoulders under one at a time. Broaden your chest. Press your upper arms down. Fold your arms across your chest. Keep your gaze toward the ceiling. Keep your head and neck still.', '05_Abdominal_and_Supine', '', NULL, 'Bridge Pose', NULL, 'Setu Bandhasana or Bridge construction
The descriptive meaning of the name is Bridge construction.
Effects: Back extensor muscles grow powerful, adrenal glands bathed in blood, strengthens neck, tones entire spine, bathes glands in blood.', true, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, 'à¤¸à¥‡à¤¤à¥à¤¬à¤¨à¥à¤§à¤¾à¤¸à¤¨', 'Setu Bandhasana (Bridge Pose)', 'In Setu Bandhasana, the gluteus maximus and hamstrings contract to lift the pelvis, promoting extension of the lumbar spine while the sternum moves towards the chin; the internal rotation of the thighs helps stabilize the pose and lift the frontal iliac spines.', 'The symbol features an open circle with a vertical axis offset to one side, representing the lifting action and spinal extension in Setu Bandhasana.', true, '/storage/v1/object/public/yoga-cards/111_master_setu_bandhasana.webp', '/storage/v1/object/public/audio-assets/111_setubandhasana.mp3', NULL, NULL, 9, '{"flow": 5, "long": 60, "short": 15, "standard": 30}', '[]', false),
	('Viranchyasana I', '144', 'ViranchyÄsana I', 'Final: 386, 387', 19, true, 302, 248, 'Assume a seated position. Place one leg in half lotus. Bring the other leg behind the neck. Clasp the hands behind the back. Hold the pose. Breathe steadily. Release the hands from the clasp. Bring the leg down from behind the neck. Release the half lotus position.', '08_Advanced_Leg_behind_Head', NULL, NULL, 'Viranchiâ€™s Pose I', '14/2/2026 4:12pm', 'Viranchyasana I
This pose is dedicated to Brahma.
Effects: strengthens back, strengthens neck.', true, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'à¤µà¤¿à¤°à¤žà¥à¤šà¥à¤¯à¤¾à¤¸à¤¨', '"The pose of Viranchi (Brahma)", Step One.', 'Viranchyasana I establishes the foundation for deeper hip opening. The adductors draw the femur inwards while the spine maintains vertical extension, preventing lumbar collapse.', 'A square frame containing an offset vertical axis line. A solid bindu resides adjacent to this line within the frame, positioned towards the lower right quadrant, symbolizing grounded asymmetry.', true, '/storage/v1/object/public/yoga-cards/144_master_viranchyasana_i.webp', '/storage/v1/object/public/audio-assets/144_viranchyasanai.mp3', NULL, NULL, 8, '{"flow": 5, "long": 60, "short": 30, "standard": 45}', '[]', false),
	('Skandasana', '136', 'SkandÄsana', 'Final: 372', 16, true, 294, 241, 'Place the leg behind the neck. Bend the trunk forward. Hold the outstretched leg. Bring the chin to the knee. This sequence enables a deeper abdominal contraction. This also provides spine exercise.', '08_Advanced_Leg_behind_Head', NULL, NULL, 'Skanda Pose', '14/2/2026 4:12pm', 'Skandasana or Skanda pose
