Effects: deeper abdominal contraction, spine exercise.', true, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'à¤¸à¥à¤•à¤¨à¥à¤¦à¤¾à¤¸à¤¨', 'Skanda''s Pose; dedicated to the God of War, Skanda', 'The pose requires deep adductor engagement in the bent leg and extension in the straight leg, cultivating strength and flexibility. The spine remains elongated, creating axial extension from the sacrum to the crown of the head.', 'Two parallel vertical lines are encased within a square frame. An open circle rests on the bottom line, centered between the parallel lines.', true, '/storage/v1/object/public/yoga-cards/136_master_skandasana.webp', '/storage/v1/object/public/audio-assets/136_skandasana.mp3', NULL, NULL, 8, '{"flow": 5, "long": 60, "short": 30, "standard": 45}', '[]', false),
	('Eka Pada Setu Bandha Sarvangasana', '099', 'Eka PÄda Setu Bandha SarvÄngÄsana (Eka PÄda UttÄna MayÅ«rÄsana)', 'Final: 260', 11, true, 229, 186, 'Begin by lying down in a supine position. Align your body into Bridge Pose Variation Bound Hands. Inhale and press the right foot firmly into the ground. Exhale and engage your core. Lift your left foot off the ground. Extend the left leg. Point your toes to the sky. Lift the pelvis to keep the hips high. Press your chest up and back. Apply Chin Lock (Jalandhara Bandha). Stay in the pose for several breaths. Exhale and lower the left leg. Return to the Bridge Pose. Slowly bring your upper back down. Lower your middle back next. Bring your lower back down last. Repeat the pose with the other leg.', '04_Inversions_Sirsasana_Sarvangasana', '; Alternate names: Eka Pada Uttana Mayurasana', NULL, 'One-Legged Bridge Pose', '14/2/2026 4:12pm', NULL, true, NULL, NULL, NULL, '117', 'à¤à¤• à¤ªà¤¾à¤¦ à¤¸à¥‡à¤¤à¥ à¤¬à¤¨à¥à¤§ à¤¸à¤°à¥à¤µà¤¾à¤™à¥à¤—à¤¾à¤¸à¤¨', 'One-Foot Bridge Construct All-Limbs Pose', 'The pose establishes core stability through engagement of the gluteus maximus and hamstrings, lifting the pelvis. Scapular adduction supports the thoracic spine to promote a posterior bend.', 'Three intersecting lines form an inverted ''Y'' shape. The central vertical line represents the spine. Two angled lines extend outwards from the base, symbolizing the single extended leg and the supporting bent leg. An equilateral triangle is positioned above the ''Y'', representing the stability of the shoulders.', true, '/storage/v1/object/public/yoga-cards/099_master_eka_pada_setu_bandha_sarvangasana_eka_pada_uttana_mayurasana.webp', '/storage/v1/object/public/audio-assets/099_ekapadasetubandhasarvangasana.mp3', 117.00, NULL, 4, '{"flow": 5, "long": 120, "short": 30, "standard": 60}', '[]', false),
	('Viparita Chakrasana in Urdhva Dhanurasana', '173', 'ViparÄ«ta ChakrÄsana in Åª. Dh.', 'Final: 488, 489, 490, 491, 492, 493, 494, 495, 496, 497, 498, 499', 26, false, 361, 301, 'Lie down on your back. Bend your knees. Place your heels close to your buttocks. Place your palms near your ears. Point your fingers toward your shoulders. Press your feet and hands into the floor. Inhale to lift your hips. Straighten your arms and legs to enter Urdhva Dhanurasana. Hold the full wheel pose. Perform a reverse somersault movement from Urdhva Dhanurasana. Swing your leg up and back. Swing your body down. Lower your legs to the floor. Stand in Tadasana. Relax your body.', '09_Backbends', NULL, NULL, 'Inverted Wheel Pose', '14/2/2026 4:12pm', 'Viparita Chakrasana in Urdhva Dhanurasana or Reversed wheel
