	('Dwi Pada Sirasana', '147', 'Dwi PÄda ÅšÄ«á¹›sÄsana', 'Final: 393, 394 | Int: 392', 24, true, 307, 253, 'Sit on the ground. Find seated balance on your tailbone. Bend your right leg. Place your right foot behind your right shoulder. Bend your left leg. Place your left foot behind your left shoulder. Lock your ankles behind your neck. Place your hands on the floor next to your hips. Press into your hands for balance. Contract your lungs and abdominal muscles tightly. Lift your body off the floor. Establish vertical balance. Maintain this position. Gently lower your body to release the pose. Release your legs.', '08_Advanced_Leg_behind_Head', NULL, NULL, 'Two-Legged Headstand', '14/2/2026 4:12pm', 'Dwi Pada Sirasana or Both feet-behind-head
