	('Hamsasana', '129', 'Háº¡msÄsana', 'Final: 356', 10, false, 284, 232, 'Begin on your hands and knees in Table Top Pose. Ensure your knees are hip-width apart. Place your palms on the mat. Spread your fingers wide. The fingers should point forward. Exhale and bend your elbows. Lower your torso. Rest your forehead between your palms. Roll your head so the crown rests on the mat. Tuck your elbows under your abdomen. Keep your elbows close together. Shift your weight forward. Engage your core muscles. Straighten your knees one by one. Keep your toes curled on the mat. Hold the pose. To exit, lower your knees to the mat. Release your arms and legs. Come to the Vajrasana pose. Take relaxed breaths.', '07_Arm_Balances', NULL, NULL, 'Swan Pose', '14/2/2026 4:12pm', 'Hamsasana or Swan pose
