Effects: The pose cures cramp in the legs and makes the leg muscles elastic, the chest is well expanded, the back becomes erect, the shoulder joints move freely.', true, NULL, NULL, '20 | I', '56', 'à¤—à¥Œà¤®à¥à¤–à¤¾à¤¸à¤¨', 'Cow Face Pose', 'In Gomukhasana, the humerus of the top arm externally rotates while adducting towards the midline, enhancing the opening of the chest; simultaneously, the bottom arm internally rotates and extends to achieve the hand clasp, promoting shoulder joint mobility.', 'The symbol is comprised of three intersecting lines, each representing a major joint involved in the asana: the shoulders, hips, and knees. The open circle signifies the unity and balance achieved through the pose, as well as the breath which sustains it.', true, '/storage/v1/object/public/yoga-cards/037_master_gomukhasana.webp', '/storage/v1/object/public/audio-assets/037_gomukhasana.mp3', 56.00, NULL, 2, '{"flow": 5, "long": 60, "short": 15, "standard": 30}', '[]', false),
	('Urdhva Dandasana', '075', 'Åªrdhva Dáº¡á¹‡dÄsana', 'Final: 188', 8, false, 184, 147, 'Begin by following the instructions for Headstand Pose. Upon release, exhale slowly. Lower your legs slowly. Engage your core. Engage your shoulders. Engage your neck. Pause halfway. Position your legs parallel to the floor. Position your legs perpendicular to your torso. Bring your knees close to each other. Engage your pelvis. Engage your hips. Press your hands into the floor. Lift your hips up. Come into a reverse tabletop position. Straighten your arms. Lift your chest up. Keep your legs straight. Engage your core to maintain the pose. Hold the pose for a few breaths. Release back down to the floor.', '04_Inversions_Sirsasana_Sarvangasana', 'Plate 188 appears in the middle of the sequence of plates for Salamba Sirasana I', NULL, 'Upward Staff Pose', '14/2/2026 4:12pm', 'Urdhva Dandasana or Upward staff
