	('Vrksasana', '002', 'Vá¹›ká¹£Äsana', 'Final: 2', 1, true, 62, 41, 'Stand in Tadasana. Bend the right leg at the knee. Place the right heel at the root of the left thigh. Rest the right foot on the left thigh. Point the toes downwards. Balance only on the left leg. Join the palms together. Raise the arms straight over the head. Extend the spine upward. Stay in the pose for a few seconds. Breathe deeply. Lower the arms. Straighten the right leg. Stand again in Tadasana. Repeat the pose on the opposite side. Balance on the right leg. Place the left heel at the root of the right thigh.', '01_Standing_and_Basic', '', NULL, 'Tree Pose', NULL, 'Vrksasana or Tree Pose
Vrksa means a tree.
Effects: Tones leg muscles, develops balance.', true, NULL, NULL, '2', '21', 'à¤µà¥ƒà¤•à¥à¤·à¤¾à¤¸à¤¨', 'vá¹›ká¹£a (tree) + Äsana (seat/pose)', 'Grounding the standing leg engages the adductors to stabilize the pelvis. Counter-traction lengthens the spine, mitigating compression and encouraging axial extension.', 'A single vertical line intersected at the base by an open circle, with a second line branching upward and outward at a 45-degree angle from the vertical line.', true, '/storage/v1/object/public/yoga-cards/002_master_vrksasana.webp', '/storage/v1/object/public/audio-assets/002_vrksasana.mp3', 21.00, NULL, 1, '{"flow": 5, "long": 60, "short": 15, "standard": 30}', '2', false),
	('Uttihita Parsvakonasana', '005', 'Utthita PÄrÅ›vakoá¹‡Äsana', 'Final: 8, 9', 4, true, 66, 45, 'Stand in Tadasana. Jump your legs four to four and a half feet apart. Turn your right foot ninety degrees right. Bend your right knee until the thigh is parallel to the floor. Ensure the shin is perpendicular to the floor. Place your right palm on the floor by the outer side of the right foot. Stretch your left arm over the left ear. Keep your chest, hips, and legs in one line. Roll the biceps forward and out as the shoulder tip presses back. Press into the back heel. Inhale deeply to lengthen the arm. Stay in the pose for thirty to sixty seconds. Repeat the actions on the other side.', '01_Standing_and_Basic', NULL, NULL, 'Extended Side Angle Pose', '14/2/2026 4:12pm', 'Uttihita Parsvakonasana or Extended lateral angle pose
Parsva means side and kona means an angle, defining the pose as an extended lateral angle position.
Effects: Reduces fat at waist, aids digestion, tones knees and thighs.', true, NULL, NULL, '4', '24', 'à¤‰à¤¤à¥à¤¥à¤¿à¤¤à¤ªà¤¾à¤°à¥à¤¶à¥à¤µà¤•à¥‹à¤£à¤¾à¤¸à¤¨', '"Extended Side Angle Pose": utthita (extended), parsva (side), kona (angle), asana (pose).', 'The pose integrates adductor engagement to ground the legs while simultaneously lengthening the spine along a diagonal axis. Core stability facilitates the opening of the chest and hip.', 'A diagonal slash descends from right to left, representing the spine''s energetic line. Concentric arcs curve outwards from the midpoint of the slash, symbolizing the opening of the side body.', true, '/storage/v1/object/public/yoga-cards/005_master_utthita_parsvakonasana.webp', '/storage/v1/object/public/audio-assets/005_uttihitaparsvakonasana.mp3', 24.00, NULL, 1, '{"flow": 5, "long": 60, "short": 15, "standard": 40}', '5', false),
	('Virabhadrasana I', '007', 'VÄ«rabhadrÄsana I', 'Final: 14 | Int: 12, 13', 3, true, 69, 48, 'Stand in Tadasana. Raise the arms over the head. Join the palms. Jump the legs four to four and a half feet apart. Turn the body to the right. Bend the right knee to a right angle. Ensure the front knee is stacked directly above the ankle. Stretch the left leg. Keep the left knee locked. Angle the left foot approximately forty-five degrees. Keep the hips at the same height, facing slightly diagonal. Keep the shoulders facing forward over the front knee. Lift the head. Gaze at the joined palms. Stay for twenty to thirty seconds. Press into the floor with the right foot. Step the left foot back up into Tadasana. Repeat the pose on the left side.', '01_Standing_and_Basic', NULL, NULL, 'Warrior I Pose', '14/2/2026 4:12pm', 'Virabhadrasana I
