	('Ardha Navasana', '036', 'Ardha NÄvÄsana', 'Final: 79 | Int: 77 Intermediate:', 2, false, NULL, NULL, 'To perform Ardha Navasana (Half Boat Pose), begin by sitting on the floor with your legs extended straight in front of you. Place your hands on the floor slightly behind your hips, fingers pointing toward your feet. Lean your torso back slightly while keeping your spine straight and chest open, ensuring you do not collapse into your lower back.

Exhale and lift your legs off the floor, keeping them straight and glued together. Simultaneously, reach your arms forward so they are parallel to the floor and aligned with your shoulders, palms facing each other or downward. Unlike the full Boat Pose, in Ardha Navasana the body is lowered closer to the ground. Lower your legs until your feet are roughly at eye level, and lower your torso so that only the sacrum and lower back remain in contact with the floor.

Keep your abdominal muscles deeply engaged to support your spine. Your neck should remain relaxed, with your gaze directed toward your toes. Hold the pose for five to ten breaths, maintaining a steady and even rhythm. To release, exhale as you slowly lower your legs and torso back to the floor.', '02_Seated_and_Lotus_Variations', '', NULL, 'Half Boat Pose', '14/2/2026 4:12pm', 'Ardha Navasana Ardha means half; Nava means a boat.

Effects: Strengthens the core and hip flexors; tones the abdominal organs and lower back.', true, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'à¤…à¤°à¥à¤§à¤¨à¤µà¤¾à¤¸à¤¨', 'Ardha (à¤…à¤°à¥à¤§) - half; Nava (à¤¨à¤¾à¤µ) - boat; Asana (à¤†à¤¸à¤¨) - pose. Literally: Half Boat Pose.', 'The pose emphasizes the structural integrity of the spine through active engagement of the core musculature. Adductor engagement stabilizes the foundation of the posture.', 'Three lines intersect at a central bindu. A vertical line ascends, representing the spine. Two angled lines emanate from the bindu, symbolizing leg and torso convergence.', true, '/storage/v1/object/public/yoga-cards/036_master_ardha_navasana.webp', '/storage/v1/object/public/audio-assets/036_ardhanavasana.mp3', NULL, NULL, 5, '{"flow": 5, "long": 60, "short": 20, "standard": 30}', '[]', false),
	('Trianga Mukhaikapada Paschimottanasana', '062', 'TriangÄ MukhaikapÄda PaschimottÄnÄsana', 'Final: 139 | Int: 138 Intermediate:', 5, true, NULL, NULL, 'Begin in Staff Pose. Keep one leg straight. Bend the other knee backward. Position the top of the bent foot on the ground near the hip. Press the top of the bent foot into the floor. Ground both sitting bones equally. Lengthen your spine. Stretch both arms forward. Grab the extended foot with both hands. Flex the extended foot. Fold forward. Bring your chin to your knee. Deepen the stretch on each exhale.', '02_Seated_and_Lotus_Variations', '', NULL, 'Three-Limbed Seated Forward Bend', NULL, 'Trianga Mukhaikapada Paschimottanasana or Three-limbed back stretch
This pose is a three-limbed back stretch.
