	('Gherandasana I', '192', 'Gheráº¡á¹‡dÄsana I', 'Final: 561, 562, 563 | Int: 558, 559, 560', 44, true, 403, 335, 'Lie prone on the floor. Bend one leg into Bhekasana. Reach back and grab the foot of the bent leg. Bring the bent foot toward the hip. Lie the thigh of the bent leg on the ground. Keep the pubic bone pressing on the ground. Inhale and lift the head and chest. Bring the other leg up into Padangustha Dhanurasana. Reach back with the corresponding arm. Grab the big toe of the lifted leg. Lift the foot and arms up as much as possible. Keep breathing continuously. The combined leg work tones the spinal column.', '09_Backbends', NULL, NULL, 'Gherandaâ€™s Pose I', '14/2/2026 4:12pm', 'Gherandasana I
