	('Maha Mudra', '058', 'MahÄ MudrÄ', 'Final: 125', 5, true, 147, 115, 'Sit on the floor in a comfortable position. Extend the right leg straight out in front. Keep the left foot tucked against the right inner thigh. Inhale deeply. Lift the arms overhead and stretch upwards. Bend forward toward the extended leg. Hook the big toe of the right leg with the thumb and forefingers. Tuck the chin so it rests in the hollow of the collar bones. Perform Jalandhara Bandha. Tighten the entire abdomen. Perform Uddiyana Bandha. Hold the breath inside. Perform Mula Bandha. Exhale slowly. Lift the head and release the hands. Straighten the arms. Raise the arms above the head. Bring the arms down to the sides as you finish breathing out. Relax the body. Repeat on the other side.', '02_Seated_and_Lotus_Variations', NULL, NULL, 'Great Seal', '14/2/2026 4:12pm', 'Maha Mudra or Great seal
