	('Ujjayi Pranayama', '203', 'UjjÄyÄ« PrÄá¹‡ÄyÄma', 'Final: 597', 1, false, NULL, 370, 'Sit in a comfortable position. Keep the back erect and rigid. Lower the head to the trunk. Rest the chin in the notch above the breast-bone. Stretch the arms out straight. Rest the back of the wrists on the knees. Join the tips of the index fingers to the tips of the thumbs. Keep the other fingers extended. Close the eyes. Look inwards. Exhale completely. Take a slow, deep steady breath through both nostrils. Fill the lungs up to the brim. Do not bloat the abdomen during inhalation. Pull the entire abdominal area back towards the spine. Hold the breath for a second or two. Exhale slowly, deeply and steadily until the lungs are completely empty. Keep your grip on the abdomen as you begin to exhale. Gradually and slowly relax the diaphragm after two or three seconds of exhalation. Wait for a second before drawing a fresh breath. Repeat the cycles for five to ten minutes. Keep the eyes closed throughout. Lie on the floor in Savasana.', '10_Restorative_Pranayama', NULL, 'I,II,III,IV,V,VI,VII,VIII,IX,X,XI,XII,XIII', 'Victorious Breath', '14/2/2026 4:12pm', 'Ujjayi Pranayama
