	('Urdhva Mukha Paschimottanasana I', '069', 'Åªrdhva Mukha PaschimottÄnÄsana I', 'Final: 168', 10, false, 173, 138, 'Balance on the buttocks. Stretch the legs up. Catch the heels. Rest the forehead on the knees. Engage the pelvic floor muscles. Pull the tummy in. Extend the spine fully. Balance on the sit bones. Bring the chin to the knee. Lift the spine from the base. Lengthen the spine up. Stay in the pose for several breaths. Release the grip on the feet. Gently lower the legs down. Relax in Dandasana.', '03_Forward_Bends', 'Plate in book not quite in numerical order with its corresponding asana', NULL, 'Upward-Facing Intense Stretch Pose I', '14/2/2026 4:12pm', 'Urdhva Mukha Paschimottanasana I or Upward face back stretch
