	('Savasana', '200', 'ÅšavÄsana', 'Final: 592', 1, false, NULL, NULL, 'Sit on a level floor with a blanket spread beneath the body. Draw a straight line on the blanket to ensure accurate physical alignment. Sit on the center of this line with the knees drawn up and the feet placed together. Lower the back vertebra by vertebra along the line until the entire spine rests on the floor. Lift the hips and use the hands to move the flesh of the buttocks away from the waist. Extend the legs fully one by one until the heels and knees are joined. Align the heels, knees, crotch, coccyx, spinal column, and the base of the skull on the straight line. Adjust the front of the body so the bridge of the nose, chin, sternum, navel, and pubis are in a single vertical plane. Check that the ears, outer corners of the eyes, and the jawbone are parallel to the floor. Stretch the back of the neck centrally and pin the inner points of the shoulder blades to the floor. Roll the skin of the upper chest from the collarbones toward the shoulder blades to broaden the chest. Rest the center of the sacrum on the floor to allow the buttocks to relax evenly. Let the feet fall outwards evenly so the big toes feel weightless. Place the hands fifteen to twenty degrees away from the body with the palms facing upwards. Bend the arms at the elbows to touch the shoulder tops before extending the triceps toward the feet. Lower the forearms and extend the hands from the wrists to the knuckles with passive fingers. Relax the muscles of the back from the trunk to the neck and the front of the body from the pubis to the throat. Close the eyelids gently and move the upper lids toward the inner corners of the eyes. Release any tightness in the forehead by slightly raising the eyebrows. Keep the root of the tongue passive and resting on the lower palate. Soften the skin of the temples, cheekbones, and the lower jaw to quieten the brain. Exhale softly and deeply while ensuring the breath flows evenly through both nostrils. Keep the head straight and parallel to the ceiling to remain anchored in the present moment. Observe the internal silence and keep the senses of knowledge passive and receptive. Maintain this state of complete physical and mental stillness for ten to fifteen minutes. Remain as a silent observer until normal activity returns to the brain. Open the eyes slowly and gently without focusing them immediately. Bend the knees and turn the head and body to one side. Stay in this side lying position for one or two minutes before repeating on the other side. Rise slowly to a seated position to avoid strain or heaviness in the head.', '10_Restorative_Pranayama', '; Alternate names: Savasana', NULL, 'Corpse Pose', NULL, 'Savasana or Corpse pose
The technique involves motionless conscious relaxation with energy flow from the back of the head to the heels.
Effects: Antidote to stresses of modern civilisation, removes fatigue, antidote for modern stress, invigorates body and mind.', true, NULL, NULL, '41', '150, 152 | I', 'à¤¶à¤µà¤¾à¤¸à¤¨', 'Åšava means ''corpse''; Asana means ''posture''. Thus, Corpse Posture.', 'Savasana requires complete muscular relaxation while maintaining awareness. This pose promotes systematic release from the periphery to the core; the structural intention is to fully ground the posterior body while suspending active thought.', 'Two parallel lines represent the grounded body. Concentric arcs originate from the space between the lines, expanding outwards and upwards, suggesting the dissolution of tension and the quietude of the mind.', true, '/storage/v1/object/public/yoga-cards/200_master_savasana.webp', '/storage/v1/object/public/audio-assets/200_mrtasana.mp3', 150.00, 'I', 5, '{"flow": 5, "long": 600, "short": 180, "standard": 300}', '212', true),
	('Utthita Trikonasana', '003', 'Utthita Trikoá¹‡Äsana', 'Final: 4, 5 | Int: 3', 3, true, NULL, NULL, 'Stand in Tadasana. Inhale deeply. Jump and spread the legs apart sideways. Raise the arms sideways in line with the shoulders. Keep palms facing down. Turn the right foot sideways ninety degrees to the right. Turn the left foot slightly to the right. Keep the left leg stretched from the inside. Tighten the left leg at the knee. Exhale. Bend the trunk sideways to the right. Bring the right palm near the right ankle. Rest the right palm completely on the floor if possible. Stretch the left arm up. Bring the left arm in line with the right arm and shoulders. Gaze at the thumb of the extended left hand. Stay in this position. Breathe deeply. Breathe evenly. Inhale. Return to the starting position. Repeat these actions on the left side.', '01_Standing_and_Basic', '', NULL, 'Extended Triangle Pose', '14/2/2026 4:12pm', 'Uttihita Trikonasana or Extended Triangle Pose
