	(349, 'Knees', NULL, '2026-04-21T03:27:06.802Z', NULL, true, 235, '[{"note": "", "side": null, "tier": null, "type": "pose", "props": [], "pose_id": "074", "duration": null, "stage_id": null}, {"note": "", "side": null, "tier": null, "type": "pose", "props": [], "pose_id": "087", "duration": null, "stage_id": null}, {"note": "", "side": null, "tier": null, "type": "pose", "props": ["chair"], "pose_id": "234", "duration": null, "stage_id": 133}, {"note": "", "side": null, "tier": null, "type": "pose", "props": [], "pose_id": "200", "duration": null, "stage_id": null}]', NULL, NULL, 'Welcome to your practice. These poses should be done to rest the knees. After this, you are able to incorporate more standing poses, paying particular attention to the alignment of the knees, to avoid strain. Sitting poses can be performed, but with careful adjustment to the bent leg, for example including sitting on folded blankets to lift the lower back and make the legs comfortable. For really stiff feet and ankles kneel with the shins on two or three blankets with the feet hanging over the edge. If pain is acute, avoid bent-leg postures and seek advice. Press Start to begin.'),
