	(2, 'Deepak Chopra Three Dosha', 'MACRO:Surya Namaskar Classical | 3 | [Sequence Link] Linked Sequence: 3 Rounds
221 | 420 | []
222 | 40 | [] Action: Massage belly, back, and legs. Focus: Firm pressure upward; move energy to the heart.
223 | 40 | [] Jhulana | Action: Hug knees to chest; rock side to side. Focus: Massage the lower back; keep neck free.
224 | 60 | [] Vajrasana | Action: Inhale, rise to kneeling; Exhale, sit on heels. Focus: Fluid, slow movement; vertical spine.
059 | 60 | [] Janu Sirsasana | Action: Fold over one straight leg. Focus: Reach through the heel; lengthen from the lower back.
087 | 180 | [I] I | | I | | I | | I | | | Action: Lift legs and hips; support back with hands. Focus: Stillness in the throat; gaze at toes.
091 | 60 | [] Halasana | Action: Lower feet over head. Focus: Stretch through heels; do not strain the neck.
031 | 30 | [] Bhujangasana I | I | | | Action: Lie on belly; lift chest. Focus: Use back muscles; expand the ribs.
025 | 45 | [] Salabhasana | Action: Lift legs and chest off floor. Focus: Lengthen the spine; breathe into the belly.
114 | 60 | [] Marichyasana III | III | | | Action: Sit and twist toward the upright knee. Focus: Twist on the exhale; keep chest open.
020 | 60 | [] Uttanasana | Action: Stand and fold forward. Focus: Gravity pulls the spine long; knees relaxed.
200 | 120 | [] Savasana | Action: Lie flat on back; palms up. Focus: Total surrender; let the body absorb the practice.
